description:
This week, we'll follow the office hours format: https://www.factual.com/blog/clojure-office-hours

If you have a Clojure project you're working on (or just some Clojure questions), bring it along to the Oracle offices to get some in-depth insight. We can go through your code with you and offer advice.

Any type of project is welcome, whether it be an exercise from a beginners' textbook or something crazy and ambitious like a game. Or maybe you just want an extra pair of eyes on that 4clojure problem you're working on. Or you want to upgrade your emacs setup. A bunch of devs will be here to help.

Food and drinks will be provided, so see you there!

Note, just in case you missed it: this meetup will be hosted at the Oracle office in central Bristol, rather than the usual location.
title: Clojure Office Hours
